
---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Header from '../components/astro/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/astro/Footer.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Privacy Policy | Tribal Installment Loans"
  description="Our privacy policy outlines how we collect, use, and protect your personal information when you use our tribal installment loan connection service."
  canonicalUrl="https://tribal-installment-loans.com/privacy-policy"
  keywords="privacy policy, tribal loans privacy, personal data protection, loan information security"
>
  <div class="flex flex-col min-h-screen">
    <Header />
    
    <main class="flex-grow pt-24">
      <section class="py-12 md:py-16 bg-gradient-to-b from-tribal-50 to-white">
        <div class="container mx-auto px-4">
          <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
            <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold mb-6 text-tribal-900">Privacy Policy</h1>
            <p class="text-lg text-tribal-600">
              Last Updated: January 15, 2024
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>
      
      <section class="py-12 bg-white">
        <div class="container mx-auto px-4">
          <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
            <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none text-tribal-700">
              <p>
                At Tribal Installment Loans, we are committed to protecting your privacy and ensuring the security of your personal information. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, disclose, and safeguard your information when you visit our website or use our services.
              </p>
              
              <p>
                Please read this Privacy Policy carefully. By accessing or using our website, you acknowledge that you have read, understood, and agree to be bound by all the terms of this Privacy Policy. If you do not agree with our policies and practices, please do not use our website or services.
              </p>
              
              <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4 text-tribal-900">Information We Collect</h2>
              
              <p>We may collect several types of information from and about users of our website, including:</p>
              
              <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mt-6 mb-3 text-tribal-900">Personal Information</h3>
              
              <p>When you apply for a loan through our website, we collect personal information such as:</p>
              
              <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
                <li>Name, address, email address, telephone number</li>
                <li>Date of birth and Social Security Number</li>
                <li>Employment information and income details</li>
                <li>Banking information, including account and routing numbers</li>
                <li>Financial history and credit information</li>
              </ul>
              
              <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mt-6 mb-3 text-tribal-900">Non-Personal Information</h3>
              
              <p>We may automatically collect certain non-personal information when you visit our website, including:</p>
              
              <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
                <li>IP address and browser type</li>
                <li>Device information and operating system</li>
                <li>Pages visited and time spent on the website</li>
                <li>Referral source and interactions with the website</li>
              </ul>
              
              <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4 text-tribal-900">How We Collect Your Information</h2>
              
              <p>We collect information directly from you when you:</p>
              
              <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
                <li>Complete and submit forms on our website</li>
                <li>Register for an account</li>
                <li>Participate in surveys or promotions</li>
                <li>Contact our customer service</li>
              </ul>
              
              <p>We also collect information automatically through technologies such as:</p>
              
              <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
                <li>Cookies and similar tracking technologies</li>
                <li>Log files and analytics tools</li>
                <li>Web beacons and pixel tags</li>
              </ul>
              
              <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4 text-tribal-900">How We Use Your Information</h2>
              
              <p>We may use the information we collect for various purposes, including:</p>
              
              <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
                <li>Processing your loan application and connecting you with tribal lenders</li>
                <li>Creating and maintaining your account</li>
                <li>Communicating with you about your account or application</li>
                <li>Sending you marketing communications (with your consent)</li>
                <li>Improving our website and services</li>
                <li>Analyzing usage patterns and conducting research</li>
                <li>Complying with legal obligations</li>
                <li>Protecting against fraud and unauthorized transactions</li>
              </ul>
              
              <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4 text-tribal-900">Disclosure of Your Information</h2>
              
              <p>We may disclose your personal information to the following third parties:</p>
              
              <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
                <li>Tribal lenders and financial institutions in our network</li>
                <li>Service providers who assist us in operating our website and business</li>
                <li>Marketing partners (with your consent)</li>
                <li>Legal and regulatory authorities, when required by law</li>
                <li>Potential buyers in the event of a business sale or merger</li>
              </ul>
              
              <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4 text-tribal-900">Data Security</h2>
              
              <p>
                We implement a variety of security measures to maintain the safety of your personal information when you enter, submit, or access your personal information. These include:
              </p>
              
              <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
                <li>Secure Socket Layer (SSL) encryption technology</li>
                <li>Data encryption and secure storage</li>
                <li>Access controls and authentication procedures</li>
                <li>Regular security assessments and monitoring</li>
              </ul>
              
              <p>
                Despite our efforts, no method of electronic transmission or storage is 100% secure, and we cannot guarantee absolute security of your information.
              </p>
              
              <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4 text-tribal-900">Your Choices</h2>
              
              <p>You have certain choices regarding the information you provide to us:</p>
              
              <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
                <li>You can review and update your account information</li>
                <li>You can opt-out of marketing communications</li>
                <li>You can adjust cookie settings in your browser</li>
                <li>You can request access to or deletion of your personal information (where applicable by law)</li>
              </ul>
              
              <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4 text-tribal-900">California Privacy Rights</h2>
              
              <p>
                If you are a California resident, you may have additional rights under the California Consumer Privacy Act (CCPA) regarding your personal information. These rights may include:
              </p>
              
              <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
                <li>Right to know what personal information we collect about you</li>
                <li>Right to request deletion of personal information</li>
                <li>Right to opt-out of the sale of personal information</li>
                <li>Right to non-discrimination for exercising your privacy rights</li>
              </ul>
              
              <p>
                To exercise these rights, please contact us using the information provided in the "Contact Us" section below.
              </p>
              
              <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4 text-tribal-900">Children's Privacy</h2>
              
              <p>
                Our website and services are not intended for individuals under the age of 18. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 18. If we become aware that we have collected personal information from a child under 18 without verification of parental consent, we will take steps to remove that information from our servers.
              </p>
              
              <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4 text-tribal-900">Changes to Our Privacy Policy</h2>
              
              <p>
                We may update our Privacy Policy from time to time. When we make changes, we will revise the "Last Updated" date at the top of this Privacy Policy. We encourage you to review this Privacy Policy periodically to stay informed about how we collect, use, and protect your information.
              </p>
              
              <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4 text-tribal-900">Contact Us</h2>
              
              <p>
                If you have any questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy or our privacy practices, please contact us at:
              </p>
              
              <p class="mt-4">
                <strong>Email:</strong> privacy@tribal-installment-loans.com<br>
                <strong>Phone:</strong> +39 3791398291<br>
                <strong>Mail:</strong> Tribal Installment Loans<br>
                Privacy Office<br>
                123 Finance Street<br>
                Suite 400<br>
                Chicago, IL 60601
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>
    </main>
    
    <Footer />
  </div>
</Layout>
